                                <note>Boulenger’s edition was based on two manuscripts, <idno type="msRef">Paris. gr. 510</idno> (9th century) and <idno type="msRef">Paris Coislin 51</idno> (10th century). For a more complete list of mss, see <ref>http://pinakes.irht.cnrs.fr/notices/oeuvre/7607/</ref> to which this fragment can be added. Only three mss appear listed in Pinakes as containing a textual lacuna, all dated 9th–10th centuries.</note>
